        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:50PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Driscoll, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Corpus Christi, Driscoll, Bishop, South Texas Botanical Gardens,
Kings Crossing Subdivision, Waldron Field, Petronila, and Chapman
Ranch.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 680 and 686.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
